lls, politics, and economic forces. Through investigating a range of contrasting cropscapes spanning millennia and the globe, the authors break open traditional historical structures of period, geography, and direction to glean insight into previously invisible actors and forces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aCropsxGeographical distribution. 0aCropsxHistory. 0aHistoriographyxMethodology. 0aPlants and civilization. 0aWorld historyxHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh1 aHahn, Barbara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLourdusamy, John Bosco, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSaraiva, Tiago, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030026842340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300268423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300268423/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY